Daud Olatunji THIRTY-one persons have lost their lives in 80 road accidents involving 291 persons in Ogun State between December 15, 2019 and January 15, 2020. The Public Relations Officer of Ogun State Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps, Babatunde Akinbiyi, disclosed this in a release on Saturday. Akinbiyi said the record was compiled by the Director, Traffic Planning, Research and Statistics of TRACE, Ajayi Babatunde. Akinbiyi said the accidents left 160 people comprising 96 males and 64 females with various degrees of injury. He said the accidents involved 11 private cars, 10 private buses, 13 commercial buses, 15 commercial cars, six motorcycles, one tricycle, 12 medium trucks, 11 heavy trucks and 13 other vehicles. Akinbiyi stated, “Ogun State Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps has recorded between Sunday, December 15, 2019 and Wednesday January 15, 2020, a total number of 80 road traffic crashes involving 11 private cars, 10 private buses, 13 commercial buses, 15 commercial cars, 6 motorcycles, one  tricycle, 12 medium trucks, 11 heavy trucks and 13 other vehicles. “During the period 291 persons were involved in road traffic crashes out of which 160 persons (96 males and 64 females) sustained various degrees of injury. Thirty-one persons (15 males and 16 females) were killed and 100 persons rescued unhurt due to prompt response to 47 emergency calls received by TRACE.” Akinbiyi said 41.93 per cent of the road crashes was caused by excessive speed, 23.78 per cent by dangerous driving, 10.99 per cent resulted from bad tyres, 3.33 per cent caused by driving against traffic and 19.97 per cent attributed to other causes. “Eighty-eight motor vehicles and 39 motorcycles were apprehended for 163 offences,” he added. Copyright PUNCH.
